@bzz ah yes, I was going to update http://zeppelin.incubator.apache.org/docs/interpreter/spark.html as the next step.
It looks like it gets stale a bit so I'll take that as a separate project.
Opened https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ZEPPELIN-368

@corneadoug :+1: for hiding the option.

> (Hide in Notebook if anything is running, Hide in paragraph if that paragraph is running or queued)

I think it should be "hide" if anything is running or queued, if we hide only in paragraph when the that paragraph is running, the user will still be able to call clear all from notebook

@corneadoug  I believe this is a default behaviour that we do on terminal (command line) as well. After firing a huge command which will result in a lots of log; run the particular command and press Ctrl-L to clear the screen. 
Or even in case of firebug console as well, console logs keep flowing, and we do clear log, just to see what appeared next.
Hence, personally I don't feel a need of either disabling or removing or giving a confirmation box.
